🧾 Project Name
B7A2

🌐 Live URL

https://assingment02-seven.vercel.app

🚀 Features
User authentication (JWT-based login system)
Role-based access control (Contributor, Maintainer)
Create, update, delete issues
View all issues with filtering and sorting
View single issue with reporter details
Secure API with middleware authentication
Centralized error handling
Database connection pooling for performance

🛠 Tech Stack
Backend: Node.js, Express.js
Language: TypeScript
Database: PostgreSQL
Authentication: JSON Web Token (JWT)
Validation: Express Middleware
Architecture: MVC + Modular Pattern
Tools: pg (node-postgres), bcrypt, dotenv

⚙️ Setup Instructions
1. Clone the repository
https://github.com/ashraf03/typescript-learning/new/main/module09/assingment02
cd your-project
2. Install dependencies
npm install
3. Setup environment variables

Create a .env file:

CONNECTIONSTRING= "postgresql://neondb_owner:npg_5Rath3bHekrS@ep-damp-resonance-aq1cd39k-pooler.c-8.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require&channel_binding=require"

PORT=8000

JWT_SECRET=asdfsfsdfdsffdh
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=asdfkldfd;afwe=kls

4. Run database migration (if applicable)
npm run db:init

5. Start development server
npm run dev
📡 API Endpoints
🔐 Auth
POST /api/auth/login → User login
📌 Issues
POST /api/issues → Create issue (Contributor, Maintainer)
GET /api/issues → Get all issues (public)
GET /api/issues/:id → Get single issue (public)
PATCH /api/issues/:id → Update issue
DELETE /api/issues/:id → Delete issue (Maintainer only)

🗄 Database Schema Summary
Users Table
id (Primary Key)
name
email
password
role (contributor | maintainer)
created_at
updated_at

Issues Table
id (Primary Key, Auto Increment)
title (max 150 chars)
description (min 20 chars)
type (bug | feature_request)
status (open | in_progress | resolved)
reporter_id (references users.id logically)
created_at
updated_at

📌 Notes

Reporter details are fetched separately (no JOIN used)
JWT payload includes: id, name, role
Connection pooling is used for PostgreSQL efficiency
Centralized error handling ensures consistent API responses

🎯 Summary

This project is a scalable backend Issue Tracking System built with Express and PostgreSQL, focusing on:

Clean architecture
Secure authentication
Role-based authorization
Efficient database handling
